9-62:Since none of the dependency algorithms has been shown to be consistently and significantly better than the others, we use all of them in our experimentation .
9-63:From the clustering techniques, we choose the best performing Cos+TD .
9-64:As a baseline, we use a combination of the baselines in each components, i.e., cos for clustering and complete link for dependencies .
9-65:Note that we need to retrain all the algorithms on the training set because our objective function to optimize is now JF, the joint F measure .
9-66:For each algorithm, we need to optimize both the clustering threshold and the dependency threshold .
9-67:We did this empirically on the training set and the optimal values are listed in table 6 .
9-68:The results on the training set, also presented in table 6, indicate that cos+TD+Simple Thresholding is significantly better than the baseline in terms of the joint F value JF, using a one tailed paired Ttest at 95% confidence level .
9-69:On the whole, we notice that while the clustering performance is comparable to the experiments in section 7.1, the overall performance is undermined by the low dependency performance .
9-70:Unlike our experiments in section 7.2 where we had provided the true clusters to the system, in this case, the system has to deal with deterioration in the cluster quality .
9-71:Hence the performance of the dependency algorithms has suffered substantially thereby lowering the overall performance .
9-72:The results on the test set present a very similar story as shown in table 7 .
9-73:We also notice a fair amount of consistency in the performance of the combination algorithms .
9-74:cos+TD+Simple Thresholding outperforms the baseline significantly .
9-75:The test set results also point to the fact that the clustering component remains a bottleneck in achieving an overall good performance. .
10-1:In this paper, we have presented a new perspective of modeling news topics
10-2:Contrary to the TDT view of topics as flat collection of news stories, we view a news topic as a relational structure of events interconnected by dependencies
10-3:In this paper, we also proposed a few approaches for both clustering stories into events and constructing dependencies among them
10-4:We developed a timedecay based clustering approach that takes advantage of temporallocalization of news stories on the same event and showed that it performs significantly better than the baseline approach based on cosine similarity
10-5:Our experiments also show that we can do fairly well on dependencies using only surface features such as cosinesimilarity and time stamps of news stories as long as true events are provided to the system
10-6:However, the performance deteriorates rapidly if the system has to discover the events by itself
10-7:Despite that discouraging result, we have shown that our combined algorithms perform significantly better than the baselines
10-8:Our results indicate modeling dependencies can be a very hard problem especially when the clustering performance is below ideal level
10-9:Errors in clustering have a magnifying effect on errors in dependencies as we have seen in our experiments
10-10:Hence, we should focus not only on improving dependencies but also on clustering at the same time
10-11:As part of our future work, we plan to investigate further into the data and discover new features that influence clustering as well as dependencies
10-12:And for modeling dependencies, a probabilistic framework should be a better choice since there is no definite answer of yes no for the causal relations among some events
10-13:We also hope to devise an iterative algorithm which can improve clustering and dependency performance alternately as suggested by one of the reviewers
10-14:We also hope to expand our labeled corpus further to include more diverse news sources and larger and more complex event structures
